glosses: to pay (give money in exchange for goods or services)

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish اودهمك, اودمك (ödemek), from Proto-Turkic *ȫte-. Perhaps related with Proto-Tungusic *xuda- and Proto-Mongolic *kudaldu-. Cognate with Turkmen ȫdemek, Azerbaijani ödəmək, Bashkir үтәү (ütəw), Southern Altai ӧдӱ- (ödü-), etc.
Compare also Dongxiang ghudandu, Manchu ᡠᡩᠠᠮᠪᡳ (udambi, “to buy”), Manchu ᡥᡡᡩ᠋ᠠ (hūda, “business”), Nanai хода (hoda, “price”),
Mongolian худалдах (xudaldax, “to trade”).
